text: Air India Express Flight 1344 was a scheduled flight from Dubai, United Arab Emirates to Kozhikode in Kerala, India. On 7 August 2020, the Boeing 737-800 skidded off the end of the runway into a gorge, where it broke into two pieces. Of the 191 people on board - including both pilots - were killed in the crash. ==References== Category:2020 in India Category:August 2020 events Category:Aviation accidents and incidents in Asia Category:2020 disasters in Asia Category:21st century in Kerala Category:Aviation accidents and incidents in 2020
